To compute \( A \circ B \), where \( \circ \) denotes the Hadamard product (also known as the entrywise product), we multiply corresponding elements of matrices \( A \) and \( B \). Given:

\[
A = \begin{pmatrix}
0 & 1 \\
1 & 0
\end{pmatrix}
\]

\[
B = \begin{pmatrix}
2 & 3 \\
4 & 5
\end{pmatrix}
\]

The Hadamard product \( A \circ B \) is:

\[
A \circ B = \begin{pmatrix}
0 \cdot 2 & 1 \cdot 3 \\
1 \cdot 4 & 0 \cdot 5
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
0 & 3 \\
4 & 0
\end{pmatrix}
\]

